Class CyclerGadget<T extends Enum<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.desht.sensibletoolbox.api.gui.Gadget

  • Type Parameters:
    T - an enum type
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AccessControlGadget, AutoBuilder.AutoBuilderGadget, ChargeDirectionGadget, EnergyFlowGadget, FilterTypeGadget, RedstoneBehaviourGadget

    public abstract class CyclerGadget<T extends Enum<T>>
extends ClickableGadget
    A gadget which can cycle through the values of the given parameterised enum and apply that value to the GUI's owning item. To use this class, extend it with a concrete enum type, implement the abstract methods, and possibly override non-abstract methods.

      • CyclerGadget

        protected CyclerGadget(InventoryGUI gui,
            int slot,
            String label,
            BaseSTBItem item)
        Constructs a cycler gadget.

        The item parameter would typically refer to a separate STB item or block from the GUI's owner. This allows a GUI on one item to configure a setting in a separate block.

        Parameters:
        gui - the GUI to add the gadget to
        slot - the GUI slot to display the gadget in
        label - the primary tooltip for the gadget
        item - the item this gadget should apply to

      • add

        public void add(T what,
       ChatColor colour,
       MaterialData texture,
       String... lore)
        Add a definition (label, button texture) for a particular value of the enum. This method should be called from the subclass's constructor for each value of the enum; for any value for which it is not called, a default texture will be created.
        Parameters:
        what - the enum value for which the texture is being defined
        colour - colour to use in the texture's tooltip
        texture - material to use for the texture
        lore - extra tooltip text
